<section class="hero wrap">
  <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span>Income Tax &middot; Section 234A/B/C</span>
  <h1>234A/B/C Interest <span class="grad-text">Calculator</span></h1>
  <p class="answer-first"><b>Interest under Sections 234A, 234B and 234C is charged at 1% per month (or part of a month).</b> 234A is for late filing of the return, 234B for paying less than 90% of assessed tax as advance tax, and 234C for shortfall in individual advance-tax instalments.</p>
</section>

<div class="panel-wrap">
  <div class="calc-panel">
    <div class="field"><label>Assessed tax = tax on total income &minus; TDS/TCS/relief (Rs.)</label><input type="number" id="t" placeholder="e.g. 200000"></div>
    <div class="section-head" style="margin:20px 0 4px"><h2 style="font-size:16px">Advance tax paid (cumulative) for 234C</h2></div>
    <div class="row2"><div class="field"><label>By 15 Jun (Rs.)</label><input type="number" id="p1" value="0"></div>
      <div class="field"><label>By 15 Sep (Rs.)</label><input type="number" id="p2" value="0"></div></div>
    <div class="row2"><div class="field"><label>By 15 Dec (Rs.)</label><input type="number" id="p3" value="0"></div>
      <div class="field"><label>By 15 Mar (Rs.)</label><input type="number" id="p4" value="0"></div></div>
    <div class="row2"><div class="field"><label>Months late in filing ITR (234A)</label><input type="number" id="ma" value="0"></div>
      <div class="field"><label>Months for 234B (Apr to payment)</label><input type="number" id="mb" value="0"></div></div>
    <div class="field"><div class="hint">234B applies only if total advance tax paid (the 15 Mar figure) is below 90% of assessed tax. Shortfalls are rounded down to the nearest Rs.100 (Rule 119A). For borderline month-end dates, count each month/part-month as per Section 234B/C.</div></div>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" style="width:100%;margin-top:6px" onclick="calc()">Calculate 234A/B/C</button>
    <div id="out"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose" style="padding-top:30px">
    <h2>How 234A, 234B and 234C work</h2>
    <p><b>234A</b> &mdash; 1% per month on unpaid tax from the due date of filing to the actual filing date. <b>234B</b> &mdash; 1% per month on (assessed tax &minus; advance tax paid) where advance tax is below 90% of assessed tax, from 1 April of the assessment year. <b>234C</b> &mdash; 1% per month on the shortfall in each instalment against the 12%/36%/75%/100% thresholds.</p>
    <div class="callout law"><b>Sections 234A, 234B, 234C, Income-tax Act</b> &mdash; simple interest at 1% per month or part thereof; shortfall rounded under Rule 119A.</div>
    <div class="callout warn"><b>Caution.</b> 234C has special relief for the first instalment where shortfall arises from capital gains, dividend or lottery income not foreseeable. This tool does not separate such income — compute advance tax on such items separately under Section 234C provisos.</div>
    <div class="faq"><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <details><summary>Can 234A and 234B apply together?</summary><p>Yes. They cover different defaults &mdash; late filing (234A) and advance-tax shortfall (234B) &mdash; and can both apply in the same year.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Is the interest simple or compound?</summary><p>Simple interest at 1% per month or part of a month. There is no compounding.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Does part of a month count as a full month?</summary><p>Yes, for all three sections any part of a month is treated as a complete month.</p></details>
    </div>
    <div class="key-takeaways"><h2>Key takeaways</h2><ul>
      <li>All three sections charge 1% per month (part = full).</li>
      <li>234A: late filing; 234B: &lt;90% advance tax; 234C: instalment shortfall.</li>
      <li>234C thresholds: 12% / 36% / 75% / 100% by 15 Jun/Sep/Dec/Mar.</li>
      <li>Shortfalls rounded down to nearest Rs.100 (Rule 119A).</li>
    </ul></div>
